The National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) has mobilised 2, 300 graduates for the 2020 Batch ‘A’ orientation course in Plateau. Ms Jennifer Laha, Head Public Relations Unit of the Corps in the state, announced this on behalf of the State Coordinator in a statement made available to News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Monday in Jos. According to Laha, the orientation exercise would hold between March 10 and March 30. She said that the formal swearing-in of the corps members would hold on March 12. “Gov. Simon Lalong of Plateau will preside over the event, while the Chief Judge of the State will administer the oath of allegiance on the corps members. “We enjoin the peace-loving people of Plateau, especially those around Mangu and environs where the permanent orientation camp is located to accord the corps members the usual hospitality the state is known for,” she said.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .